Tin Consumption to Increase 2% Worldwide This Year, Timah Says

-- B y   C h a n y a p o r n   C h a n j a r o e n
-- 
2011-08-25T07:17:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-25/tin-consumption-to-increase-2-worldwide-this-year-timah-says.html
Global refined-tin consumption will
rise 2 percent this year from 2010, said PT Timah, the world’s
second-largest producer.  The company’s refined-metal production dropped 5.4 percent
to 18,455 metric tons during 2011’s first six months compared
with the year before, the Pangkalpinang, Indonesia-based company
said today in a statement accompanying first-half results.  Yunnan Tin Co. is the world’s largest producer based on
2010 output, according to industry group ITRI Ltd.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chanyaporn Chanjaroen in Singapore at 
 cchanjaroen@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 James Poole  at   jpoole4@bloomberg.net . 